This paper deals with the statistical modeling of traffic on network links, which is a problem related to computer networks and communication (cs.NI). It also discusses anomalous traces, which can be related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper uses state-of-the-art statistical techniques, which can be related to machine learning and data analysis (cs.SI). The paper also discusses predicting service level agreements and link capacity estimation, which can be related to information theory (cs.IT) and performance analysis (cs.PF).
